Overall Performance

Load the data and omit the missing values.

First, let’s look at the total number of shots, total number of games, average number of shots per game,average points per game, field goal percentage and total points.

#Total number of games
player_shot_chart %>% summarise(number_of_games = n_distinct(game_id)) 
##   number_of_games
## 1            1558
#Total number of shots
player_shot_chart %>% summarise(total_number_o_shots = n())
##   total_number_o_shots
## 1                25697
#Average number of shots per game
player_shot_chart %>% group_by(game_id) %>%
  summarise(shot_number = n()) %>%
  summarise(average_shot_per_game = mean(shot_number)) 
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   average_shot_per_game
##                   <dbl>
## 1                  16.5
#Average points per game
player_shot_chart %>% 
  group_by(game_id) %>% 
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>% 
  summarise(average_point = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(average_point_total = mean(average_point))
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   average_point_total
##                 <dbl>
## 1                16.1
#Overall field goal percentage
player_shot_chart %>% 
  summarise(n = n(), made_shots = sum(shot_made_flag)) %>%
  mutate(field_goal_percentage = made_shots / n)
##       n made_shots field_goal_percentage
## 1 25697      11465              0.446161
#Total points 
player_shot_chart %>%
  group_by(game_id) %>%
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>%
  summarise(average_point = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(point_total = sum(average_point)) 
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   point_total
##         <dbl>
## 1       24712

Kobe Bryant’s Home - Away Performance

Now, let’s look at his performance at home and away.

#Extracting the home games
player_h <- player_shot_chart %>% filter(str_detect(matchup, "vs.")) 

#Total number of shots at home
player_h %>% summarise(total_shots_at_home = n())
##   total_shots_at_home
## 1               12485
#Total number of games at home
player_h %>% summarise(total_games_at_home = n_distinct(game_id)) 
##   total_games_at_home
## 1                 778
#Average number og shots at home
player_h %>% 
  group_by(game_id) %>%
  summarise(shot_number = n()) %>%
  summarise(average_shot_home = mean(shot_number)) 
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   average_shot_home
##               <dbl>
## 1              16.0
#Average points at home
player_h %>% 
  group_by(game_id) %>% 
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>% 
  summarise(average_point_h = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(average_point_home = mean(average_point_h)) 
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   average_point_home
##                <dbl>
## 1               15.9
#Field Goal percentage at home
player_h %>% 
  summarise(n=n(), made_shots = sum(shot_made_flag)) %>%
  mutate(field_goal_percentage_at_home = made_shots / n) %>%
  select(field_goal_percentage_at_home)
##   field_goal_percentage_at_home
## 1                     0.4564678
#Total points at home
player_h %>% 
  group_by(game_id) %>%
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>%
  summarise(a = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(total_points_at_home = sum(a))
## # A tibble: 1 x 1
##   total_points_at_home
##                  <dbl>
## 1                12267

Kobe Bryant’s performance by conference

#Extracting East and West teams from each other
conf <- player_shot_chart %>% 
  mutate(opponent_c = ifelse(opponent %in% c("ATL", "BOS", "BKN","CHA","CHI", "CLE", "DET","WAS","PHI","TOR","NJN","NYK","IND","MIA","MIL","ORD"), "East","West"))

#Total number of games per conference
conf %>% group_by(opponent_c) %>% summarise(total_games_conf = n_distinct(game_id))
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   opponent_c total_games_conf
##   <chr>                 <int>
## 1 East                    475
## 2 West                   1083
#Total number of shots per conference
conf %>% group_by(opponent_c) %>% summarise(total_shots_conf = n())
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   opponent_c total_shots_conf
##   <chr>                 <int>
## 1 East                   7681
## 2 West                  18016
#Average number of shots per conference 
conf %>% group_by(opponent_c) %>%
  summarise(total_games_conf = n_distinct(game_id),shot_number = n())%>%
  mutate(avg_shot = shot_number / total_games_conf) %>%
  select(opponent_c, avg_shot)
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   opponent_c avg_shot
##   <chr>         <dbl>
## 1 East           16.2
## 2 West           16.6
#Field goal percentage per conference 
conf %>% 
  group_by(opponent_c) %>%
  summarise(n = n(), made_shots = sum(shot_made_flag)) %>%
  mutate(percentage = made_shots / n) %>%
  select(opponent_c, percentage)
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   opponent_c percentage
##   <chr>           <dbl>
## 1 East            0.435
## 2 West            0.451
#Average points per conference
conf %>% 
  group_by(opponent_c,game_id) %>% 
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>% 
  summarise(average_point_c = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(average_point_conf = mean(average_point_c))
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   opponent_c average_point_conf
##   <chr>                   <dbl>
## 1 East                     15.5
## 2 West                     16.4
#Total points per conference 
conf %>%
  group_by(opponent_c,game_id)%>%
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>% 
  summarise(t = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(total_point_conference = sum(t)) 
## # A tibble: 2 x 2
##   opponent_c total_point_conference
##   <chr>                       <dbl>
## 1 East                         7230
## 2 West                        17482

player_shot_chart %>% group_by(shot_zone_basic) %>% summarise(total_shots = n())

#Field Goal percentage by shot zone basic 
player_shot_chart %>%
  group_by(shot_zone_basic) %>%
  summarise(n = n(), made_shots = sum(shot_made_flag)) %>%
  mutate(percentage = made_shots / n )%>%
  select(shot_zone_basic, percentage)
## # A tibble: 7 x 2
##   shot_zone_basic       percentage
##   <fct>                      <dbl>
## 1 Above the Break 3         0.329 
## 2 Backcourt                 0.0167
## 3 In The Paint (Non-RA)     0.454 
## 4 Left Corner 3             0.371 
## 5 Mid-Range                 0.406 
## 6 Restricted Area           0.618 
## 7 Right Corner 3            0.339
#Total points by shot zone basic
player_shot_chart %>%
  group_by(shot_zone_basic,game_id)%>%
  filter(shot_made_flag == 1) %>% 
  summarise(t = sum(points)) %>%
  summarise(total_point_basic = sum(t))
